# Discord Server Discovery Personalization Prototype - Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Build a high-fidelity prototype of Discord's Server Discovery page to demonstrate the business value of personalization and SEO structured data. The prototype will be a React web app featuring a side-by-side comparison of a generic discovery experience versus a personalized one, along with a standalone tab for an SEO structured data demonstration.

## User Review Required
No immediate user review required, but I will prompt the user to approve the plan before proceeding with execution.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Foundation
- Initialize a new React project using Vite in the `discord-server-discovery-prototype` directory.
- Create `src/styles/tokens.css` to define the Discord dark mode color palette, typography (DM Sans), and spacing.

### Data Layer
#### [NEW] src/mockData.js
- Defines the `mockUser` profile representing a dormant user.
- Defines ~12-16 `server` objects across various categories with relevant personalization signals (e.g., `friendsInServer`, `matchScore`, `personalizedReason`).

### UI Components
#### [NEW] src/components/ReasonChip.jsx
- Renders the small pill above the server name mapping to personalization signals (Returning, Friends, Interests, Trending, New).
#### [NEW] src/components/ServerCard.jsx
- The core server card component with hover lift effect, server icon, join button, and optional ReasonChip.
#### [NEW] src/components/CategorySidebar.jsx
- Sidebar containing category filters mimicking Discord's categories.
#### [NEW] src/components/PanelHeader.jsx
- Sticky top bar for the Discovery panels showing the panel label and metric summary.
#### [NEW] src/components/PMNotesPanel.jsx
- Collapsible sidebar for Growth and SEO hypotheses.
#### [NEW] src/components/ServerModal.jsx
- Modal overlay simulating the Discord server preview.

### SEO Components
#### [NEW] src/components/JsonLdBlock.jsx
- Component to display syntax-highlighted JSON-LD structured data.
#### [NEW] src/components/SerpPreview.jsx
- Component to simulate a Google Rich Result SERP preview.
#### [NEW] src/components/StructuredDataDemo.jsx
- Standalone view comparing the current Discord `<head>` without schema vs. the proposed state with `Organization` and `DiscussionForumPosting` schema.

### Main Layout
#### [NEW] src/ServerDiscoveryPrototype.jsx
- The hero two-panel layout comparing "Discovery Today" and "With Personalization".
#### [MODIFY] src/App.jsx
- Wires up the tabs/toggles for switching between the main side-by-side demo and the SEO layer.
#### [MODIFY] index.html
- Import `DM Sans` from Google Fonts.

### Documentation
#### [NEW] FIGMA_SPEC.md
- Document component inventory, color/text styles, spacing, and prototype flow notes as requested.
#### [NEW] README.md
- Setup instructions and demo script.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Verification
- Run the React dev server locally to ensure all components render without errors.
### Manual Verification
- Review the side-by-side layout to confirm visual indistinguishability from Discord's UI.
- Verify that the SEO layer accurately highlights JSON-LD and renders the SERP preview pixel-accurately.
- Confirm that the UI animations (e.g., stagger-in and hover lift) function smoothly.
